reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 30, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Amazing for Individuals with Autism!
reviews.reviewText: I just RAN to Amazon to review this toothbrush. I've had an awful relationship with my teeth my whole life, starting from when I had braces and headgear as a kid. I am autistic and suffer from some pretty frustrating sensory issues, but I never really considered my mouth to be a part of that. I had orthodontists and dentists all over me for several years, so I figured that was the reason why I developed severe dentalphobia. The minute I graduated, I swore off the dentist. That was a decade ago.Brushing my teeth has always been a chore, and a miserable one at that. I would go long periods without brushing just because I hated it so much, and I could never put a finger on why. I thought recently that maybe it was the stinging sensation of mint toothpaste, so I went on Amazon to get a gentler toothpaste and just threw this toothbrush in the cart as a recommended item.I seriously started tearing up the moment I started brushing with it. It was so much better. No prickliness, no stabbing at my gums, no scratchy noise that seemed to always be too loud. It was softer, quieter. It didn't bother my sore gums at all. I told my husband, it feels like brushing my teeth with velvet, as weird as that sounds. I can't even believe what a difference it made.It was a pretty emotional experience for me because I never realized that this is how easy it could've been all my life. That this is how other people manage to brush their teeth without it being such a miserable experience. This is the first time in almost fifteen years that I've felt like maybe I can have a normal, healthy relationship with my teeth. I will ONLY be using this brush from now on.

It is a much more comfortable experience than brushing with a normal brush.Note: if you have dentures or invisalign, these are very good brushes for cleaning them! Very gentle.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for elder care - wish I’d found these sooner
reviews.reviewText: I got these for my mom, who I was taking care of in her last years. She hated having her teeth brushed. Regular toothbrushes, like the kind you buy at the local drugstore are fine for most of us, but even the kind labeled ‘extra soft’ were too harsh for my mother’s aging teeth. I tried all kinds of options: the little brushes for cleaning between your teeth, silicone baby brushes that you slip onto your finger, those hospital lollipop wedge things that come in plastic wrappers. I even tried Q-tips. Then one day out of boredom I tried some random word that I can’t even remember in the search on Amazon and found these. I gave them a try. They’re the only toothbrushes that didn’t make my mother scream and cry during tooth brushing. They’re nice and soft, and do a good job of holding their shape.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars not well thought out
reviews.reviewText: These are very soft. They are so tightly packed that the best they can accomplish is a polished surface but due to the tightly packed bristles they can't work between the teeth at all. If your goal is to polish the front and back surface of your teeth, then this is your weapon. But good teeth cleaning is much more about getting in and around the gums and between the teeth and into any small crevises. This brush can NOT do that. I think it is anti educational for those seeking healty mouths.I also noticed, as I was attempting to work between my teeth, that a few of the fine bristles dislodged and end up in my mouth. They are so fine that I can't imagine how uncomfortable it would be to swallow one of these as I think it would be difficult to dislodge. Last complain is when I did use it to polish the interior surface of my front teeth it slipped multiple times and jabbed the inside where my lips and gum meet, which for some will guarentee a canker sore! I think the handle contributes to this issue. It is so thin and difficult to hold while applying any pressure. SO, not a fan of the idea and feel bad for people who love this so much without realizing how much they are missing by cleaning between their teeth with a brush, which is a well kept secret evidently.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 23, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Rethink how you brush
reviews.reviewText: Revolutionary toothbrush. The small head let’s you get in and around your entire tooth surface unlike any traditional toothbrush. Brush in circles. Brush side to side. Brush up and down. If you feel rough plaque with your tongue simply concentrate on that area every time you brush and eventually it will feel smoother.After each use it’s important to rinse the bristles under running water and to spread the bristles far apart with a finger and rinse clean all the way down to the bottom. Then I dry the handle and bristles with a paper towel. I use two toothbrushes a day: the white one in the morning and the black one at night.I’ve had my first set for 2 months and have not had any issues with yellowing or foul smells.The top surfaces of my molars used to have stains in the crevices. With a bit of attention with these toothbrushes the stains have lightened substantially. You don’t need to push down hard, just let the bristles do their thing. These manual toothbrushes have cleaned my teeth better than any expensive battery toothbrush. I brush in zones making sure I get every surface. These toothbrushes are a delight to use. Very gentle on your gums yet tenacious on your teeth. They are my new tooth brushing super power.( btw, my husband is a dentist.)

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Destroys enamel after 2 years of usage
reviews.reviewText: Do not buy these. We loved them at first because they made our teeth feel more clean than they ever have. Then after a year and a half of usage I noticed my teeth got super sensitive to heat and cold. Now my enamel has been rubbed off and my teeth are ruined. The dentist doesn’t think a toothbrush would cause it, but that is the only change I made in my oral care. My partner also has sensitive teeth now, so we are throwing these away. Do your longterm self a favor and absolutely do not buy these products.
